definitions.definition: A small corner formed by two walls ; an alcove .
examples: There was a small broom for sweeping ash kept in the nook between the fireplace bricks and the wall.

definitions.definition: A hidden or secluded spot ; a secluded retreat .
examples: The back of the used book shop was one of her favorite nooks ; she could read for hours and no one would bother her or pester her to buy.
